Three people were killed and five others were left critically injured following a shooting incident in Soweto on Sunday. Police spokesperson Lungelo Dlamini says, “Police in Dobsonville are investigating the murder of three people and also five others that were wounded. They fired shots, two died at the scene, one died at hospital and five others are still recovering at the hospital.” It is understood that three gunmen stormed a house in Dobsonville, Soweto and began opening fire. Police say they do not know the motive for the shooting at this stage.